(1, 'Sui Network?s TVL Growth Is Incredible In Just 2 Months', 18, 22, '<div style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><div style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Sui Network’s TVL Skyrockets, Defying Market Trends</div></div><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">This surge reflects the network’s robust capabilities, boasting top-tier security, consistently low gas fees, and remarkable throughput, positioning it as a frontrunner in the burgeoning DeFi ecosystem. Over the past 90 days, the Sui Network’s TVL has surged by over 30%, underscoring Sui’s growing influence.</p><div style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><div style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://cnews24.ru/uploads/b71/b71cc7e74f9de010eeb34aa932c887121fc7a15a.png\" style=\"border-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\"></div></div><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">However, the SUI token has experienced a pronounced downtrend, marking lower lows since reaching its annual high of $0.45 on September 11. The crypto’s price broke through the formidable $0.6 support level and found a new foothold near $0.47.</p><h2 style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 700; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 48px; color: rgb(56, 56, 56);\">Sui Network’s Advantages and Blockchain Standing</h2><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Sui Network distinguishes itself as a smart contract platform managed by a consortium of validators, aligning with traditional blockchain systems in function. An exceptional feature of this platform is its capacity to process the majority of transactions in parallel, ensuring scalability and minimal latency for uncomplicated transactions like payments and asset transfers.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Another noteworthy advantage offered by the Sui Network lies in its gas fee management. The network provides stable gas fees per epoch, each lasting 24 hours and overseen by the Validators council. This departure from minute-to-minute fluctuations ensures price stability within daily cycles.</p>', '2024-11-01 08:35:56', '2024-11-04 06:58:49', 1, 'Sui-Network’s-TVL-Growth-Is-Incredible-In-Just-2-Months', '58353531c27cca229e863f7ec7c0f5b0.jpg'),
(13, 'Analyst Updates Outlook on Chainlink, Avalanche, Fantom and One Altcoin That?s Exploded Over 700% in Matter of Weeks', 18, 22, '<p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">A popular crypto trader is updating his outlook on Chainlink (LINK) as the digital asset continues to chop around.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Pseudonymous trader Altcoin Sherpa tells his 196,200 followers on the social media platform X that blockchain oracle Chainlink is likely going to take months before breaking out of a persistent trading range.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><em style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">“LINK: still one of the best coins in terms of overall crypto infrastructure, but it is still one that is chopping around.</em></p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><em style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Would consider just buying this one and letting it sit for six months-plus and then selling it much higher later. This isn’t a good active trade in my opinion.”</em></p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Looking at the analyst’s chart, LINK has traded in a range with a high of $9.33 and a low of $5.53 since May 2022.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Chainlink is trading for $6.28 at time of writing, up 1.7% in the last 24 hours.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The trader is also looking at layer-1 projects, which have dropped in prominence throughout the current crypto cycle. However, he predicts some will be trading for higher values from their current prices a year from now.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Weighing in on Ethereum (ETH) competitor Avalanche (AVAX), the trader’s chart shows AVAX is retesting a potential bottom at $9.82.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Avalanche is trading for $10.07 at time of writing, up 1.2% in the last 24 hours.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Next, the trader looks at smart contract platform Fantom (FTM). His chart suggests Fantom could bounce after touching the $0.202 level, which it last retested nearly a year ago.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Fantom is worth $0.203 at time of writing, up 0.8% in the last 24 hours.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Lastly, the trader weighs in on the crypto gambling platform Rollbit’s native token RLB, which has soared from a low of $0.0189 on June 11th to $0.154 at time of writing, a 714% increase.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">He predicts RLB could decline to retest the support level at $0.135, or even lower at $0.126, after failing to hold the $0.178 level.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><em style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">“RLB: Had nice moves today due to the stake hack but I still think the chart itself looks like crap. I’m going to hold off on buying this one for now.”</em></p>', '2024-11-01 08:36:28', '2024-11-04 07:00:06', 1, 'Analyst-Updates-Outlook-on-Chainlink,-Avalanche,-Fantom-and-One-Altcoin-That’s-Exploded-Over-700%-in-Matter-of-Weeks', '5b4a3e9c08d5ef3eef03e91c0a7e47f4.jpg'),
(14, 'AI and blockchain will \"reshape sectors\" and create new markets from scratch ? Moody\"s', 18, 22, '<p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Artificial intelligence (AI) and blockchain technologies have reached a “tipping point” and are set to shrink established industries while creating new ones, forecasts a report from Moody’s Investors Service published on Sep. 6.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">According to the authors, the combined impact of AI and distributed ledger technologies (DLTs), such as blockchain, has effects “far beyond corporate balance sheets,” and “will likely reshape entire sectors, leading established industries “to shrink or disappear altogether while creating new markets from scratch.” The report notes:</p><blockquote style=\"border-width: 0px 0px 0px 3px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-color: rgb(226, 226, 226); border-image: initial; outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(245, 245, 245); margin-top: 35px; margin-bottom: 35px; padding: 33px 33px 18px; quotes: none; font-size: 18px; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif;\"><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7;\">“History has shown that transformative technologies can shrink established sectors shrink or wipe them out entirely […] AI will drive the emergence of new sectors, possibly in content generation, mobility, education, or healthcare fields. DLT has already led to the emergence of cryptocurrencies and decentralized finance, although the track record of these segments has been uneven over the past 18 months.”</p></blockquote><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The report highlights that AI will boost economic growth by increasing productivity through task automation, partially offsetting the effects of aging and shrinking populations in many countries. As for DLT, the benefits include fostering financial inclusion and modernizing payment systems. However, it is unlikely that these benefits will materialize before the next decade.</p><div style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://cnews24.ru/uploads/4d3/4d3f919ce73cdac0ec92e28edef1f56a59a53ea1.png\" style=\"border-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\"><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7;\"></p><div style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><em style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">How AI and DLT will transform organizations’ strategies. Source: Moody’s Investors Service.</em></div></div><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">When considering the impact on global financial markets, the authors outline that AI and DLT will improve process efficiency and create new products, thereby enhancing credit profiles for financial firms, as long as financial, regulatory, and cybersecurity risks are properly addressed.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">“The coming transformation will bring process efficiency and new products, but also amplify existing risks and give rise to new ones,” reads the report, adding that the “interaction of risk and opportunity will be transmitted to debt issuer credit profiles through five broad channels, with impact varying by sector and issuer strategy.”</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Measures of credit risk that will be influenced by the technologies include business strategy and implementation, financial performance, governance and risk management, and industry and economy-level changes.</p><blockquote style=\"border-width: 0px 0px 0px 3px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-color: rgb(226, 226, 226); border-image: initial; outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(245, 245, 245); margin-top: 35px; margin-bottom: 35px; padding: 33px 33px 18px; quotes: none; font-size: 18px; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif;\"><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7;\">“The overall economic and financial effects of technological changes, including the policy and strategic shifts they prompt, are likely to be positive. However, there will be considerable differences in how the costs and benefits of progress are distributed among people, companies, and countries.”</p></blockquote>', '2024-11-04 07:14:46', '2024-11-07 09:59:24', 1, 'AI-and-blockchain-will-\"reshape-sectors\"-and-create-new-markets-from-scratch-?-Moody\"s', 'b39aff1af1a1533896dd283163350bb4.jpg'),
(16, 'Bitrock Emerges as a Strong Contender in Layer 2 Space', 18, 22, '<ol style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 35px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; line-height: 2; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Bitrock, a layer 2 EVM-compatible sidechain, offers lower gas fees and high throughput to users.</strong></li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">The network’s native token BROCK currently holds a market cap of $6.7 million.</strong></li></ol><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The Layer 2 blockchain ecosystem is continually evolving, with projects like Polygon, Arbitrum, Immutable X, and Mantle leading the way. In this competitive space, where numerous innovative projects enter, distinguishing the best among them can be challenging. However, Bitrock has captured the community’s attention by establishing itself as a cost-efficient and fast layer 2 EVM-compatible sidechain.</p><h3 style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 700; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 36px; color: rgb(56, 56, 56);\"><em style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Bitrock Adds Unique Benefits to the Layer 2 Landscape</em></h3><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Bitrock forayed into the blockchain scene with its stealth launch on July 13. The project set itself apart by funding its development from the team’s own resources and completing it just two months before launch. Unlike many other Layer 2 solutions, Bitrock is not a fork. It maintains a total supply equal to its circulating supply, with no locked or vested tokens, ensuring no further dilution.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">One of Bitrock’s standout features is its core team’s KYC verification with Assure DeFi, a partner working closely with the FBI, the US Attorney’s Office, and various government entities. Notably, Bitrock recently underwent a comprehensive audit with CTDSEC, a blockchain security firm that audited projects such as XRP, Ethereum, and DEXTools. Bitrock’s top score in this audit signifies its commitment to security and reliability.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Bitrock employs a Proof-of-Authority (PoA) consensus mechanism, enabling faster, cheaper, and more scalable transactions. Remarkably, users benefit from lower gas fees, with transactions costing as little as $0.00001 each. Furthermore, with a block time of 2 seconds and a commendable throughput of 12,000 transactions per second, Bitrock surpasses the capabilities of established Layer 2 solutions.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">In addition to these advantages, Bitrock’s native decentralized exchange (DEX) — Rockswap — is set to introduce a multichain integration layer, first with Ethereum. This enables the buying and selling of tokens on their native chains without the need for external swaps or gas fees in native tokens. Additionally, the L2 chain’s token builder utility simplifies the process of launching tokens by deploying a standard preloaded contract. This facility is accessible to anyone, even those with no coding or technical expertise.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Bitrock also encourages staking with annual percentage yields (APY) of 30% for Ethereum side staking and 60% for mainnet staking, enticing users to participate in securing the network. Currently, over 40% of the total supply is staked, indicating strong community engagement.</p><h3 style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 700; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 36px; color: rgb(56, 56, 56);\"><em style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Bitrock on the Path to Success?</em></h3><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Bitrock established rapid integration with various blockchain tools and platforms over the past few months. The layer-2 solution is integrated on prominent platforms such as crypto exchange Bitmart, launchpad protocol Pinksale, and Trust Wallet Swapping and renowned crypto applications such as DEXTools, Dexview, Geckoterminal, Sphynx Labs and Avedex.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">This adaptability ensures that Bitrock can be seamlessly incorporated into any wallet that supports custom networks, expanding its accessibility to users. Additionally, Bitrock’s approach to launching official partner projects involves a rigorous vetting process to ensure security and value addition to the chain.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">In return for passing this process, Bitrock offers projects marketing and project support — pre and post-launch activities — on its channels as well as other various incentives. Three official partner projects have already been launched on Bitrock including Rockswap.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">At press time, the native token — Bitrock (BROCK) — held a market capitalization of $6,749,877 and traded at the price of $0.06749.</p>', '2024-11-04 07:21:01', NULL, 1, 'Bitrock-Emerges-as-a-Strong-Contender-in-Layer-2-Space', 'fda28b4d556152c9f2ac806f33d1d477.png'),
(17, 'CertiK Names the Reason for DNS Hijacking on DeFi', 18, 22, '<p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Millions of digital assets have been stolen by cyber adversaries via DNS hijacking attacks for phishing purposes, targeting users’ wallet seed phrases, or creating deceptive webpages that closely resemble legitimate sites.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Attacks on Domain Name Systems (DNSs) play a crucial role in the internet’s infrastructure, providing insights into security incidents in Web 2 that have directly affected the Web3 industry. However, transitioning to decentralized frontends has emerged as a practical way to tackle these challenges, according to a recent report by CertiK.</p><h2 style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 700; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 48px; color: rgb(56, 56, 56);\">DNS Hijacking of DeFi Protocols</h2><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">DNS hijacking is an attack that targets a core component of Internet infrastructure. It has the potential to render a public DNS service inaccessible in certain scenarios, or it can be employed to reroute users to malicious websites, in other cases.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Typically, the attacker manipulates the DNS by substituting the mapping (DomainName, Legitimate IP) with (DomainName, MaliciousServer IP). This tampering enables them to intercept future users’ DNS queries, directing them to fraudulent websites without the users’ awareness, CertiK explained.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Users inadvertently access these deceitful sites via the compromised servers, exposing themselves to potential phishing attacks and the downloading of malware that can compromise their devices.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">CreamFinance and PancakeSwap reported DNS hijacking attacks in 2021, two public RPC gateways offered by Ankr for Polygon and Fantom wallets were compromised via a DNS hijacking attack the following year. During the same period, Cronos-based DEX MM.Finance, Curve Finance, Celer Protocol, Fantom-based SpiritSwap, and Polygon-based QuickSwap also reported frontend breaches as a result of a DNS hijack attack.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">These incidents essentially highlighted the significant impact of vulnerabilities in Web2 on the Web3 ecosystem due to the interconnected security of these two domains.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">CertiK said that the persistent challenge of DNS credential theft and highlighted vulnerabilities arising from third-party domain service providers pose a significant challenge to Web3 projects. The core Web3 protocols themselves were not inherently flawed; rather, it was the traditional centralized domain infrastructure that left them susceptible to these issues.</p><h2 style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 700; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 48px; color: rgb(56, 56, 56);\">Solution</h2><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">CertiK emphasized the need for adopting the combination of IPFS and ENS which demonstrates the potential of decentralized and DLT-based solutions in reducing DNS hijacking attacks. These systems prioritize content authenticity, minimize points of failure, and substantially lower the vulnerabilities associated with centralized control and authority.</p><blockquote style=\"border-width: 0px 0px 0px 3px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-color: rgb(226, 226, 226); border-image: initial; outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(245, 245, 245); margin-top: 35px; margin-bottom: 35px; padding: 33px 33px 18px; quotes: none; font-size: 18px; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif;\"><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7;\">“The move towards decentralized infrastructure, along with continuous strengthening of both human and technological defenses, has become essential for the future security of Web3 projects and their users.”</p></blockquote>', '2024-11-04 07:22:06', NULL, 1, 'CertiK-Names-the-Reason-for-DNS-Hijacking-on-DeFi', 'bb4dd83d613643bf461aa1ee70e79f8b.jpg'),
(18, 'Coinbase L2 Base suffers block production stall, team says fix deployed', 8, 10, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\nnormal;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#636363\">Coinbase’s layer-2\r\nnetwork, Base, suffered a block production stall on Tuesday.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\nnormal;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#636363\">According to a status\r\npage, the Base team said it identified the issue and had “deployed a fix.”<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\nnormal;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#636363\">“We have deployed a\r\nfix and are starting to see recovery of block production and gossip,” the team\r\nwrote roughly 30 minutes after it announced the investigation.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\nnormal;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#636363\">In a previous post,\r\nthe Base team wrote that it was “investigating a stall in production of\r\nblocks.”<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\nnormal;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#636363\">“Users may have issues\r\nsubmitting transactions. We are actively investigating and will provide updates\r\nas we have them,” the team said earlier Tuesday in a post on the network’s\r\nstatus page.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\nnormal;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#636363\">The problem stemmed\r\nfrom a stalled production of blocks, which therefore caused transaction\r\nsubmission issues. According to the incident report, Base’s mainnet is impacted\r\nwhich led to the lack of block production.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\nnormal;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#636363\">Users on X, formerly\r\nTwitter, were quick to notice the issue and flag it.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:normal;vertical-align:baseline\"><b><i><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#636363;border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:\r\nnone windowtext 0in;padding:0in\">Wait is Base down?</span></i></b><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#636363\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:normal;vertical-align:baseline\"><b><i><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#636363;border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:\r\nnone windowtext 0in;padding:0in\">No blocks in 8 mins?\r\npic.twitter.com/tk5jOLZbI0</span></i></b><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#636363\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:normal;vertical-align:baseline\"><b><i><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#636363;border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:\r\nnone windowtext 0in;padding:0in\">— rpc mert | helius.dev (@0xMert_) September\r\n5, 2023</span></i></b><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#636363\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\nnormal;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#636363\">The layer-2 network,\r\nbuilt on Optimism’s OP stack, went live in early August after Coinbase\r\nannounced its plans to build it earlier this year.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\nnormal;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#636363\">On launch day, the\r\ntotal bridge value exceeded $150 million.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\nnormal;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#636363\">In the weeks following\r\nthe announcement, Base announced over 140 integrations.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\nnormal;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#636363\">Blockworks previously\r\nreported that Base has been “unusually successful” in attracting volume from\r\nboth cross-chain transactions and DeFi activity.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\nnormal;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#636363\">Coinbase did not\r\nimmediately return a request for comment.<o:p></o:p></span></p>', '2024-11-04 07:23:07', '2024-11-07 10:24:28', 1, 'Coinbase-L2-Base-suffers-block-production-stall,-team-says-fix-deployed', 'bca00e9e64795a42af6cb5bf4477b607.jpg');

