(12, 'Shah holds meeting with NE states leaders in Manipur', 6, 7, '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(25, 25, 25); font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;; font-size: 16px;\">New Delhi: BJP president Amit Shah today held meetings with his party leaders who are in-charge of 11 Lok Sabha seats spread across seven northeast states as part of a drive to ensure that it wins the maximum number of these constituencies in the general election next year.</span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(25, 25, 25); font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;; font-size: 16px;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(25, 25, 25); font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;; font-size: 16px;\"><webviewcontentdata style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(25, 25, 25); font-family: &quot;Noto Serif&quot;; font-size: 16px;\">Shah held separate meetings with Lok Sabha toli (group) of Arunachal Pradesh, Tripura, Meghalaya, Mizoram, Nagaland, Sikkim and Manipur in Manipur, the partys media head Anil Baluni said.<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Baluni said that Shah was in West Bengal for two days before he arrived in Manipur. The BJP chief would reach Odisha tomorrow.</webviewcontentdata><br></p>', '2018-06-30 19:11:44', '2024-11-04 07:38:43', 0, 'Shah-holds-meeting-with-NE-states-leaders-in-Manipur', '7fdc1a630c238af0815181f9faa190f5.jpg'),
(13, 'Chainlink (LINK) Price Surges Outperforming Bitcoin, Ethereum, and More', 11, 13, '<h1 class=\"cryptro-single-article-title\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.2; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 25px; color: rgb(52, 52, 52); letter-spacing: 0.5px;\"><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Chainlink’s LINK token performed better than the top 20 cryptocurrencies in the last seven days, as the digital asset gained 14%. Its price performance is remarkable, considering other major cryptocurrencies’ prices performed poorly during the same period.</strong></p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Commencing the week at $6.09, LINK peaked at $7.21 earlier today before dropping to $7.12 as of press time.</p></h1><h2 style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 700; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 48px; color: rgb(56, 56, 56);\">Chainlink (LINK) Price Outperforms</h2><h1 class=\"cryptro-single-article-title\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.2; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 25px; color: rgb(52, 52, 52); letter-spacing: 0.5px;\"><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;\">The primary catalyst behind LINK’s robust performance is the heightened network activity within the Chainlink ecosystem. The network address activity hit a 2-month high on September 21 as nearly 4,000 unique addresses interacted with it.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;\">This surge in network activity can be attributed to the increasing adoption of the Cross-Chain Interoperability Protocol (CCIP) by DeFi developers and traditional financial institutions.</p><div style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://cnews24.ru/uploads/cc6/cc6f68eb45fab7a2bdb0e88fec444be6ef1cabfc.png\" style=\"border-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\"><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7;\"></p><div style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Chainlink Address Activity. Source: Santiment</div></div><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Furthermore, Chainlink’s recent collaboration with Swift, a major interbank messaging infrastructure provider, resulted in a successful tokenization test involving prominent global banks. As financial institutions increasingly embrace tokenization, Chainlink’s adoption and utility are poised for substantial growth.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Despite its impressive performance in the past week, LINK remains 86% below its all-time high of $52.</p></h1><h2 style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 700; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 48px; color: rgb(56, 56, 56);\">Top 20 Cryptocurrencies Remain Flat</h2><h1 class=\"cryptro-single-article-title\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.2; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 25px; color: rgb(52, 52, 52); letter-spacing: 0.5px;\"><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;\">While LINK’s exceptional price performance stands out, the generally muted levels of the crypto market allowed the Oracle token to shine. Among the top 20 cryptocurrencies by market cap, only Solana’s SOL and Ripple’s XRP recorded an increase of more than 2% during the previous week.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Bitcoin maintained a range-bound trajectory between $26,000 and $27,000 throughout the week, concluding with minimal price change.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Santiment noted the current bearish sentiment surrounding Bitcoin, writing that traders were aggressively shorting it on certain exchanges. However, it added that this action could help push BTC’s price to $30,000.</p><div style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://cnews24.ru/uploads/b2f/b2f4563fccda498890b434443cb0ab5e93489f19.png\" style=\"border-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\"><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7;\"></p><div style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Bitcoin Traders Increasingly Short the Asset. Source: Santiment</div></div><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Meanwhile, Ethereum had a less favorable week as it turned inflationary and experienced a 2.4% decline, slipping below the $1,600 mark. Besides that, network activity has considerably dropped, leading to transaction fees dropping to yearly lows.</p></h1>', '2024-11-04 07:39:06', NULL, 1, 'Chainlink-(LINK)-Price-Surges-Outperforming-Bitcoin,-Ethereum,-and-More', 'd5897665a0151d7a54f83b801b29ce09.jpg'),
(14, 'Cryptocurrency Whale Sells All Its Altcoins After Continuous Losses', 11, 13, '<h1 class=\"cryptro-single-article-title\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.2; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 25px; color: rgb(52, 52, 52); letter-spacing: 0.5px;\"><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;\">An important Chainlink (LINK) whale seems to have sold all of his altcoins after losing a large amount of money.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Whale with short address 0xb0a sold $143,206 LINK for $964,769 at an average price of $6.74.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;\">Whale 0xb0a is known for its rapid trading cycles and completed three such cycles with LINK, resulting in a total loss of $49,261 (-2.52%).</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;\">In the first cycle, the whale traded 200k USDT and 16,150 UNI ($397k total) on August 9 for 52,319 LINK at an average price of $7.60. However, on August 12, all LINKs were sold for $385,733 at an average price of $7.37, resulting in a loss of $11,822 (-2.97%).</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;\">In the second cycle, the whale exchanged 576,870 USDT for 75,347 LINK at an average price of $7.66 on August 14 and 15. Whale sold all assets for $553,187 on August 15, at an average price of $7.34, just before the LINK price dropped sharply. This resulted in a loss of $23,683 (-4.11%).</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;\">In the last cycle, the whale bought 143,203 LINK, paying $978,525 between September 18 and September 20, paying an average of $6.83.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;\">However, the day the unfortunate whale sold all these tokens at $6.74, where the LINK price suddenly dropped. The price of the token is trading at $6.94 at the time of writing this article. Whale lost $13,000 in its last transaction.</p><div style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://cnews24.ru/uploads/e4d/e4d21dce0142c9efd0e0114e6041ec49a7bd56b3.png\" style=\"border-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\"><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7;\"></p><div style=\"text-align: left; border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px;\">Balinanın kripto para alım ve satımı yaptığı bölgeleri gösteren grafik. (SpotOnChain)</div></div></h1>', '2024-11-04 07:40:11', NULL, 1, 'Cryptocurrency-Whale-Sells-All-Its-Altcoins-After-Continuous-Losses', '17fd03cee003acd4dfae791960bd7de7.jpg');
INSERT INTO `tblrecentposts` (`id`, `PostTitle`, `CategoryId`, `SubCategoryId`, `PostDetails`, `PostingDate`, `UpdationDate`, `Is_Active`, `PostUrl`, `PostImage`) VALUES
(15, 'Ethereum Merge anniversary — 99% energy drop but centralization fears linger', 11, 13, '<p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">One year after its historic transition to proof of stake, Ethereum has seen a massive reduction in energy use and a marked improvement in access to the network, however, a number of technical issues still mark the road ahead.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The Merge was executed on Sept. 15, 2022 — an event that saw the Ethereum mainnet merging with a separate proof-of-stake blockchain called the Beacon Chain.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The most noticeable improvement to Ethereum post-merge was the seismic shift from an energy-guzzling proof-of-work (PoW) consensus mechanism to PoS, which saw the Ethereum network drastically reduce its total power consumption.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">According to data from The Cambridge Centre for Alternative Finance, the Ethereum network has seen its energy use drop more than 99.9% from the approximately 21 terawatt hours of electricity it used while running under PoW.</p><div style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://cnews24.ru/uploads/3fb/3fb245c607d72e74234dfce3bf3688af569d763e.png\" style=\"border-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\"><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7;\"></p><div style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><em style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">The Merge has reduced Ethereum’s power consumption by more than 99%. Source: CCAF</em></div></div><h3 style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 700; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 36px; color: rgb(56, 56, 56);\">Ethereum turns deflationary</h3><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Outside of using less power, The Merge also saw the Ethereum network become economically deflationary, meaning that the number of new Ether (ETH) issued to secure the network has been outpaced by the amount of ETH removed from supply forever.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">According to data from the Ethereum data provider ultrasound.money, a little more than 300,000 ETH (worth $488 million at current prices) has been burned since The Merge. At current burn rates, the total supply of ETH is being reduced at a rate of 0.25% per year.</p><div style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://cnews24.ru/uploads/a7f/a7f307bf00a72369ab17ef0552b5c9cb5028df0b.png\" style=\"border-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\"><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7;\"></p><div style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><em style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Change in ETH supply since the Merge. Source: ultrasound.money</em></div></div><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">While many proponents believed that the price of Ethereum would surge in response to this new deflationary pressure, the hopes of a dramatic increase in the price of ETH were buffeted by a series of macroeconomics headwinds such as the banking crisis and spiking inflation.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Notably, the growth of ETH paled in comparison to the growth in the price of Bitcoin (BTC) in the first quarter of this year, with the flagship crypto asset seeming to benefit from much of the traditional financial instability brought about by the banking crisis.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Price action aside, the central theme of the proof-of-stake upgrade was the introduction of stakers in place of miners to secure the network.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The subsequent Shapella upgrade in April 2023 drove ETH in huge droves towards staking. The top beneficiaries of this shift were the liquid staking providers such as Lido and Rocket Pool.</p><h3 style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 700; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 36px; color: rgb(56, 56, 56);\">Liquid staking takes over</h3><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Since the Merge, liquid staking providers have come to dominate the Ethereum landscape, with more than $19.5 billion worth of ETH currently staked by way of liquid staking protocols, according to data from DeFiLlama.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">At the time of publication, Lido is by far the largest staking provider, accounting for 72% of all staked ETH.</p><div style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://cnews24.ru/uploads/ffa/ffae3e05e5244c2676e69b13cd7466ffb864fa20.png\" style=\"border-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\"><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7;\"></p><div style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><em style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Lido currently accounts for 72% of all staking on Ethereum. Source: DeFiLlama</em></div></div><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">However while many Ethereum advocates including Labry CEO Lachlan Feeny, have praised the switch to staking for removing the barriers of expensive, sophisticated hardware for mining, one of the primary concerns with the rise of liquid staking has been the level of control granted to staking providers, in particular Lido Finance.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">“Liquid staking is ultimately good for the network as it ensures that the governance of the network is not restricted only to the wealthy. However, it has also led to the rise of its own problems,” Feeny told Cointelegraph.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">At least five Ethereum liquid staking providers working towards imposing a 22% limit rule, in a move to ensure the Ethereum network remains decentralized — though Lido voted not to take part.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Notably, Lido voted by a 99.81% majority not to self-limit back in June, leading Ethereum advocate Superphiz to declare that the the staking providers had “expressed an intention to control the majority of validators on the beacon chain.”</p><blockquote style=\"border-width: 0px 0px 0px 3px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-color: rgb(226, 226, 226); border-image: initial; outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(245, 245, 245); margin-top: 35px; margin-bottom: 35px; padding: 33px 33px 18px; quotes: none; font-size: 18px; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7;\">Lido voted by a 99.81% majority not to self-limit. They have expressed an intention to control the majority of validators on the beacon chain.https://t.co/T16rTdM3gm</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7;\">— superphiz.eth ️ (@superphiz) August 31, 2023</p></blockquote><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">This move has led to widespread concerns over the potential centralization of validation on Ethereum.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">“Lido presently controls 32.26% of all staked Ether on the network worth over $14 billion. In the long run I am confident that Ethereum is better off with liquid staking than without it, however, there are many challenges that still need to be overcome,” Feeny concluded.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Feeny also noted that the most pressing concern for Ethereum in the immediate future was the growing regulatory pressure against crypto and blockchain in the United States more broadly.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">“Regulatory bodies, particularly in the U.S. appear to be hellbent at the moment on eliminating the U.S.-based blockchain industry,” he said.</p><blockquote style=\"border-width: 0px 0px 0px 3px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-color: rgb(226, 226, 226); border-image: initial; outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(245, 245, 245); margin-top: 35px; margin-bottom: 35px; padding: 33px 33px 18px; quotes: none; font-size: 18px; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif;\"><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7;\">It would be devastating for Ethereum and the global blockchain community if it becomes too difficult for blockchain companies to operate in the US.”</p></blockquote><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Outside of staking, client diversity also remains a central issue. On Sept. 5, Vitalik Buterin took to the stage at Korea Blockchain Week to discuss the six key problems that need addressing to solve the problem of centralization.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Currently, the majority of the 5,901 active Ethereum nodes are being run through centralized web providers like Amazon Web Services, which many experts claim leaves the Ethereum blockchain exposed to a centralized point of failure.</p><div style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://cnews24.ru/uploads/0b0/0b01d8afcd3783b12cf281ebdfcb8cf8ca921f59.jpeg\" style=\"border-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\"><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7;\"></p><div style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><em style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Distribution of Ethereum nodes from web service providers. Source: Ethernodes</em></div></div><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">In Buterin’s view, in order for Ethereum to remain sufficiently decentralized in the long-term it needs to be easier for everyday people to run nodes, which means drastically reducing costs and hardware requirements for node operators.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Buterin’s primary solution was the concept of statelessness, which removes the reliance on centralized servers by reducing data requirements for node operators to near-zero.</p><blockquote style=\"border-width: 0px 0px 0px 3px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-color: rgb(226, 226, 226); border-image: initial; outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(245, 245, 245); margin-top: 35px; margin-bottom: 35px; padding: 33px 33px 18px; quotes: none; font-size: 18px; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif;\"><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7;\">“Today, it takes hundreds of gigabytes of data to run a node. With stateless clients, you can run a node on basically zero.”</p></blockquote><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">While this was Buterin’s most prominent concern for the centralization issue, he explained that these problems may not be solved for another 10 to 20 years</p>', '2024-11-04 07:40:51', NULL, 1, 'Ethereum-Merge-anniversary-—-99%-energy-drop-but-centralization-fears-linger', 'd13b98f472cee416dd5273b447016892.jpg'),
(16, '100 Million XRP Moved to Ripple as Price Readies New Move', 11, 13, '<p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Crypto data tracker Whale Alert reports a substantial amount of XRP being moved in the last 24 hours. The move that drew attention was made to a Ripple wallet.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">According to Whale Alert, 100 million XRP worth $49,977,350 were transferred from an unknown wallet to Ripple.</p><div class=\"twitter-tweet twitter-tweet-rendered\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; display: flex; max-width: 550px; width: 550px;\"><iframe id=\"twitter-widget-0\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"0\" allowtransparency=\"true\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" class=\"\" title=\"X Post\" src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/embed/Tweet.html?dnt=false&amp;embedId=twitter-widget-0&amp;%3D%3D&amp;frame=false&amp;hideCard=false&amp;hideThread=false&amp;id=1703054497684070441&amp;lang=en&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fcryptogem.io%2F100-million-xrp-moved-to-ripple-as-price-readies-new-move%2F&amp;sessionId=ba5dee3099dd3cc89548d54f2b1dc22f78001f6c&amp;theme=light&amp;widgetsVersion=2615f7e52b7e0%3A1702314776716&amp;width=550px\" data-tweet-id=\"1703054497684070441\" style=\"border-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; position: static; visibility: visible; width: 550px; height: 298px; display: block; flex-grow: 1;\"></iframe></div><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"></p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">While the rationale behind the move remains unknown, it might be a wallet reshuffle. Since the move was done from an unknown wallet to a named wallet, this might be the case. Another speculation might be an OTC trade that happens outside a traditional crypto exchange setting.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">XRP, the fifth-largest cryptocurrency by market cap, is utilized by Ripple to move money across borders. Ripple’s ODL is a cross-border payment solution that leverages the XRP cryptocurrency as a bridge asset.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">As reported, Ripple’s Vice President Emi Yoshikawa clarified the decision to “consolidate” ODL services under the moniker “Ripple Payments,” adding that ODL may be difficult for outsiders to understand at first glance.</p><h2 style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 700; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 48px; color: rgb(56, 56, 56);\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">XRP targets next major move</strong></h2><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">At the time of writing, XRP was marginally down in the last 24 hours to $0.497.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Largely, the XRP price fluctuated between $0.436 and $0.558 in recent weeks. After four days of positive price action, the XRP price recovered to a high of $0.508 on Sept. 15. On the upside, the daily MA 200 barrier at $0.517 remains a key level to watch going forward in the short term.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">If buyers push the price above the MA 200, it might imply that selling pressure is easing. This might spark a strong rally targeting the overhead barrier of $0.56. This level may once again pose a stumbling obstacle.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">If the price falls below $0.56, it might suggest that range-bound price activity may continue for a little longer. The next major move might commence in either of these scenarios: if the XRP price sustains above $0.56 or if there is a drop in the XRP price below $0.41.</p>', '2024-11-04 07:41:22', NULL, 1, '100-Million-XRP-Moved-to-Ripple-as-Price-Readies-New-Move', '319596d287fff71664d548cebba5d5ee.jpg'),
(17, 'Optimism Transfers 130M OP Tokens For Fund Management', 11, 13, '<p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Key Points:</strong></p><ul style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 35px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; line-height: 2; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><em style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Optimism initiates a planned transfer of 130 million OP tokens for fund management, ensuring community transparency.</em></li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><em style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Arbitrum’s governance token ARB hits an all-time low at $0.747, while the OP token trades at $1.33, with ARB showing signs of recovery.</em></li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><em style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Both Optimism and Arbitrum maintain strong user retention rates, reflecting user satisfaction, and have airdropped tokens to early adopters</em></li></ul><h5 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 700; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 22px; color: rgb(56, 56, 56);\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Optimism, a prominent Ethereum scaling solution, recently&nbsp;announced&nbsp;a planned internal transaction involving the transfer of 130 million OP tokens between wallets for fund management purposes. The project’s intent is to keep the community informed about this strategic move.</strong></h5><div class=\"wp-block-image\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\" style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; padding: 0px; display: table; max-width: 100%; clear: both;\"><a href=\"https://coincu.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/image-487.png\" class=\"strip gdlr-core-ilightbox gdlr-core-lightgallery\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; transition: background 300ms, color 300ms, border-color 300ms; color: rgb(84, 84, 84);\"><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-217777\" title=\"Optimism Transfers 130M OP Tokens For Fund Management 1\" src=\"https://coincu.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/image-487.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" srcset=\"https://coincu.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/image-487.png 800w, https://coincu.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/image-487-300x225.png 300w, https://coincu.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/image-487-768x576.png 768w, https://coincu.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/image-487-750x563.png 750w\" alt=\"Optimism Transfers 130M OP Tokens For Fund Management\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" data-pin-no-hover=\"true\" style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%; border-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: bottom; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></a></figure></div><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">In the crypto market,&nbsp;Arbitrum‘s governance token ARB experienced a significant drop on Tuesday, hitting a new all-time low of $0.747, as reported by CoinMarketCap. Meanwhile, OP was trading at $1.33. Presently, ARB has made a slight recovery, stabilizing at $0.798, matching yesterday’s price, while OP has seen a modest increase, reaching $1.36.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The tumultuous start to the week in the crypto world resulted in Arbitrum’s market capitalization slipping below that of its rival, Optimism.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Both Optimism and Arbitrum have consistently maintained their positions as the top&nbsp;Ethereum&nbsp;scaling solutions. What’s less known is their ability to retain a substantial user base actively participating on their respective mainnets. High user retention rates indicate satisfaction with the projects’ offered use cases.</p><div class=\"code-block code-block-1\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><div class=\"coinzilla\" data-zone=\"C-62162a8542492ed5554\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></div></div><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Furthermore, both Optimism and Arbitrum have rewarded their early adopters with airdropped tokens, fostering community engagement.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Optimism’s recent price resurgence is not unprecedented, given its previous prominence in the digital currency landscape. The sustained growth of OP tokens over the past seven days reflects the confidence and support of its buyers, underscoring the project’s resilience.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">In conclusion, Optimism’s strategic token transfer and its ability to maintain an engaged user base signal its ongoing relevance and potential in the Ethereum scaling ecosystem.</p>', '2024-11-04 07:41:46', NULL, 1, 'Optimism-Transfers-130M-OP-Tokens-For-Fund-Management', '355d8f299fc03f2ec6f8fb38c5dc3c39.jpg');
