(20, 'Ethereum Price Reaches Support, Can ETH Start A Steady Increase Again?', 11, 13, '<p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><em style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Ethereum price extended losses and tested the $2,300 support. ETH is now attempting a recovery wave above the $2,340 level and might test $2,390.</em></p><ul style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 35px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; line-height: 2; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Ethereum started a fresh decline below the $2,420 and $2,400 levels.</li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">The price is trading below $2,400 and the 100-hourly Simple Moving Average.</li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">There was a break above a connecting bearish trend line with resistance near $2,340 on the hourly chart of ETH/USD (data feed via Kraken).</li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">The pair attempt a fresh increase if it clears the $2,390 and $2,400 levels.</li></ul><h2 style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 700; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 48px; color: rgb(56, 56, 56);\">Ethereum Price Revisits $2,300</h2><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Ethereum price struggled to start a fresh increase above the $2,550 and $2,580 resistance levels. ETH started a fresh decline and traded below the $2,400 support like Bitcoin.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">There was a move below the $2,350 level. A new weekly low was formed near $2,302 and the price is now consolidating losses. There was a minor increase above the $2,330 level. The price climbed above the 23.6% Fib retracement level of the downward move from the $2,479 swing high to the $2,302 low.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">There was also a break above a connecting bearish trend line with resistance near $2,340 on the hourly chart of ETH/USD. Ethereum is now trading below $2,400 and the 100-hourly Simple Moving Average. On the upside, the price is facing resistance near the $2,365 level.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The next hurdle could be $2,390 or the 50% Fib retracement level of the downward move from the $2,479 swing high to the $2,302 low. The next major resistance is now near $2,400. A clear move above the $2,400 level might start a decent increase. In the stated case, the price could rise toward the $2,480 level.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://cnews24.ru/uploads/095/095e81a92cde7c45a26de529d62d78d1827f05a9.png\" style=\"border-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\"></p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Source: ETHUSD on TradingView.com</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The next key hurdle sits near the $2,500 zone. A close above the $2,500 resistance could start another steady increase. In the stated case, Ether price could rise toward the $2,650 zone.</p><h2 style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 700; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 48px; color: rgb(56, 56, 56);\">Another Decline in ETH?</h2><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">If Ethereum fails to clear the $2,390 resistance, it could start another decline. Initial support on the downside is near the $2,320 level.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The next key support could be the $2,300 zone. A downside break below the $2,300 support might send the price further lower. In the stated case, Ether could test the $2,250 support. Any more losses might send the price toward the $2,200 level.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Technical Indicators</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Hourly MACD<strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">&nbsp;–&nbsp;</strong>The MACD for ETH/USD is losing momentum in the bearish zone.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Hourly RSI<strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">&nbsp;–&nbsp;</strong>The RSI for ETH/USD is now below the 50 level.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Major Support Level – $2,300</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Major Resistance Level – $2,390</p><div style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Disclaimer: The article is provided for educational purposes only. It does not represent the opinions of NewsBTC on whether to buy, sell or hold any investments and naturally investing carries risks. You are advised to conduct your own research before making any investment decisions. Use information provided on this website entirely at your own risk.</div>', '2024-11-04 07:46:04', NULL, 1, 'Ethereum-Price-Reaches-Support,-Can-ETH-Start-A-Steady-Increase-Again?', '594ec8c99cdb3b975026804996fd6650.jpg'),
(21, 'Breaking News: Terraform Labs Files For Bankruptcy', 11, 13, '<div id=\"story-highlights\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><div class=\"widget-title the-global-title\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><div class=\"the-subtitle\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Story Highlights</div></div><ul style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 35px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; line-height: 2;\"><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Earlier last week, a U.S. federal judge delayed the trial against Terraform Labs and Do Kwon to allow extradition.</li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Terraform Labs now seeks constitutional protection via Chapter 11 as it only has between $100 million and $500 million in assets and liabilities</li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Do Kwon is charged with orchestrating a $40 billion crypto fraud, which triggered the 2022 crypto bear market.</li></ul></div><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The challenges facing Terraform Labs and its founder Do Kwon recently escalated after the Montenegro justice system approved the extradition to the United States or South Korea. The United States Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) recently gained the upper hand after a federal judge&nbsp;ruled&nbsp;that Terra LUNA tokens are unregistered securities</p><h2 id=\"h-terraform-labs-files-for-chapter-11-bankruptcy-protection-nbsp\" class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 700; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 48px; color: rgb(56, 56, 56);\">Terraform Labs Files for Chapter 11 Bankruptcy Protection</h2><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">According to&nbsp;court filings&nbsp;made public on January 21, Terraform Labs filed a voluntary petition for non-individuals filing for bankruptcy protection under Chapter 11 in the United States Court of Delaware. Notably, Terraforms Labs indicated that it has between $100 million to $500 million in estimated liabilities. Similarly, the distressed crypto company noted that it has between $100 million and $500 million in assets, which is a drop in the desert compared h to the $40 billion wiped out during the implosion in early 2021.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">In a separate statement, Terraform Labs Chris Amani indicated that the recent action will enable the company to continue working towards resolving its legal challenges.</p><h2 id=\"h-market-implication\" class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 700; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 48px; color: rgb(56, 56, 56);\">Market Implication</h2><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Following the Terraform Labs’ Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection in the United States, all the gains made by the respective tokens – including TerraClassicUSD (USTC), Terra LUNA, and Terra Luna Classic – had been obliterated. With the bankruptcy case likely to drag the existing case filed by the US much longer, more losses could be expected in the coming months as more investors liquidate their positions for crypto projects with better fundamentals. In November last year, Terraforms Labs injected $15 million into Terra LUNA to improve liquidity.</p>', '2024-11-04 07:46:27', NULL, 1, 'Breaking-News:-Terraform-Labs-Files-For-Bankruptcy', '9686bcad9586a87d141b1f4bb09670f2.jpg'),
(22, 'Bitcoin ETFs buy 95,000 BTC as assets under management hit $4 billion', 11, 13, '<p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The “Newborn Nine” Bitcoin ETFs have collectively amassed 95,000 BTC, with collective assets under management (AUM) nearing $4 billion, according to available data.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">According to Bloomberg ETF analyst Eric Balchunas, this remarkable inflow of capital highlights the growing investor appetite for digital assets and the increasing acceptance of cryptocurrencies in mainstream finance.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Balchunas pointed out that most ETFs typically experience a drop in trading volume each day after launch. However, the Newborn Nine have continued to post record volume, with the fifth day of trading seeing a 34% increase in volume.</p><h2 style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 700; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 48px; color: rgb(56, 56, 56);\">$1B club</h2><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">BlackRock’s IBIT and Fidelity’s FBTC have led the pack in growth. Both funds have seen substantial inflows of over $1.2 billion each within this short period and each of them holds a little over 30,000 Bitcoin.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">While Fidelity’s FBTC has slightly higher inflows, BlackRock’s IBIT leads in AUM, holding $1.4 billion compared to Fidelity’s nearly $1.3 billion.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Other notable ETFs include Invesco’s ETF, which had its best day on Jan. 19, attracting over $63 million, though its total AUM hasn’t surpassed $200 million. VanEck’s ETF has shown similar performance and broke the $100 million mark in AUM on day six of trading.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Meanwhile, Valkyrie Investments and Franklin Templeton’s AUM stood at $71.7 million and $48.6 million, respectively, on Jan. 19. WisdomTree has yet to break the $10 million mark.</p><h2 style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 700; font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 48px; color: rgb(56, 56, 56);\">Grayscale outflows</h2><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">This substantial capital influx into the newly launched Bitcoin ETFs has outpaced the outflows from the Grayscale Bitcoin Trust (GBTC), which saw its AUM decrease by $2.8 billion in the same period.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">GBTC has seen a reduction in its spot Bitcoin shares, amounting to a loss of $1.62 billion in the first four days. This suggests a shift in investor preference towards the new ETFs, which offer regulatory clarity and ease of access.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Despite the volatile nature of Bitcoin, which saw a sell-off in the same period, these ETFs have been successful. This success is partly attributed to redirecting outflows from GBTC to these new spot Bitcoin ETFs.</p>', '2024-11-04 07:46:50', NULL, 1, 'Bitcoin-ETFs-buy-95,000-BTC-as-assets-under-management-hit-$4-billion', '95bd5e0b6a0ece6946f3798e360b710f.jpg'),
(23, 'NFT Video Startup Glass Falls to Crypto Bear Market', 11, 13, '<p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Glass, a venture-backed crypto startup that sought to monetize NFT videos, is falling prey to the bear market; its founders are walking away.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Co-founders Sam Sends and Varun Iyer posted on X (formerly Twitter) Friday that they will “end active development” of Glass Protocol after determining the demand for digital, tradeable video NFTs was too low to continue.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">“The market for video NFTs can no longer sustain Glass’ development,” Iyer said. Sends struck a similar tone: “Unfortunately, we have come to the conclusion that there is not sustainable demand for video NFTs.”</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The two-and-a-half-year-old startup is the latest victim to a sustained downturn in crypto trading that has struck the NFT space particularly hard. Trading volumes are down bad for all forms of on-chain collectibles, be they the well-known “blue chip” Bored Apes but especially for smaller projects like Glass, which never really caught fire.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The idea of Glass was to give online content creators a platform for minting and selling their videos directly to their fans, where they might make more money than, say, on YouTube. Its founders saw the blockchain as bringing more transparency to this process, and also permanence, by storing them in a decentralized manner.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">“We really want to find a way to help everyone profit,” Sends said in a November 2021 podcast hosted by Arweave, the protocol’s decentralized file storage system of choice. “It’s a new way to express and own and share what you care about.”</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Indeed, the NFTs created through Glass will continue to exist alongside the website and protocol, the founders said. But they won’t continue working on the protocol, all but dooming its future growth.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Glass raised $5 million last September from investors including TCG Crypto and 1kx. It’s unclear if the protocol ran out of runway or has any of its venture capital remaining. Sends and Iyer did not immediately respond to a request for comment.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">In recent months, the founders pivoted Glass from the Solana blockchain to Ethereum, the protocol’s original home</p>', '2024-11-04 07:48:10', NULL, 1, 'NFT-Video-Startup-Glass-Falls-to-Crypto-Bear-Market', '52cb2eb2b789366ab7e596292cfed403.png'),
(24, 'Will Ethereum Hold Critical Support At $1,600?', 11, 13, '<p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">On September 6, Ark Invest made headlines by filing for the first-ever Ethereum spot exchange-traded fund (ETF) in the United States.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">This groundbreaking move had only a mild impact on its price, which briefly touched $1,650 the following day before sliding back. The gains stemming from this significant development have almost completely dissipated.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">In a separate incident, Ethereum‘s co-founder, Vitalik Buterin, fell victim to hackers who infiltrated his X account, the rebranded Twitter following its acquisition by Elon Musk.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">These malevolent actors posted phishing links, attempting to deceive Buterin’s followers with a dubious “commemorative” non-fungible token (NFT) scam. Reports suggest that multiple NFTs were pilfered in the aftermath of the breach.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Remarkably, ETH’s price has remained relatively steady in the wake of this cyberattack. Trading above the $1,600 hard support level reflects the current confidence among bullish investors.</p><div style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><div style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://cnews24.ru/uploads/e07/e0753bb41253fad65b640b0c0905b25bb55cd182.png\" style=\"border-color: rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\"><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7;\"></p><div style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">ETH price chart.&nbsp;<em style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Source: TradingView</em></div></div></div><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The focus now shifts to key price levels, with $1,655 (the 23.6% Fibonacci level) and $1,730 (the 38.2% Fibonacci level) in sight. However, these levels are contingent on favorable market conditions. If Bitcoin continues in a bearish trend, Ethereum may struggle to maintain its grip on the $1,600 support mark.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(230, 230, 230); outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(99, 99, 99); font-family: Ubuntu, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">In conclusion, Ethereum’s price journey continues to be influenced by market sentiment, with the ETF application and hacking incident serving as recent catalysts. Traders are now closely monitoring crucial price levels as the cryptocurrency market navigates its course.</p>', '2024-11-04 07:49:01', NULL, 1, 'Will-Ethereum-Hold-Critical-Support-At-$1,600?', '347df074acb0f0e430c3ece4ce8d7424.jpg');
